**Description*
The project aimed at improving healthcare delivery by first understanding the energy needs of 238 Primary Healthcare facilities in Nigeria and then providing sustainable solutions to improve facility capabilities and meeting the needs of the community including underserved population, especially in resource constraint settlements. 

This dashboard shows findings from the energy assessment, highlighting PHCs with dire need of energy access and other needs. The visualizations can be interacted using geospatial layers and filters.
